# 🧩 Architecture simple et propre

## 1. Type de tracking (contrat stable)

```ts
// infrastructure/analytics/types.ts

export type TrackEvent = {
  event: string;
  payload?: Record<string, any>;
};
```

---

## 2. Implémentation GTM (isolée)

```ts
// infrastructure/analytics/gtmTracker.ts

import { TrackEvent } from "./types";

declare global {
  interface Window {
    dataLayer: any[];
  }
}

export const trackEvent = (event: TrackEvent) => {
  if (typeof window === "undefined") return;

  window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];

  window.dataLayer.push({
    event: event.event,
    ...event.payload,
  });
};
```

👉 ici tu encapsules 100% GTM
👉 React ne sait même pas que GTM existe

---

## 3. “API métier” de tracking (IMPORTANT)

Ça c’est ton niveau propre.

```ts
// infrastructure/analytics/buttonTracking.ts

import { trackEvent } from "./gtmTracker";

type ButtonClickParams = {
  gtmId: string;
  action?: string;
  context?: string;
};

export const trackButtonClick = ({
  gtmId,
  action = "click",
  context,
}: ButtonClickParams) => {
  trackEvent({
    event: "button_click",
    payload: {
      gtm_id: gtmId,
      action,
      context,
    },
  });
};
```

👉 ça devient TON langage applicatif d’analytics

